<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idb5593349-47c4-11f1-9665-b3e99855dc0d" identifier="/us/usc/t6/s722"><num value="722">§ 722.</num><heading> Urban Search and Rescue Response System</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="idb559334a-47c4-11f1-9665-b3e99855dc0d" identifier="/us/usc/t6/s722/a"><num value="a" class="bold">(a)</num><heading class="bold"> In general</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">There is in the Agency a system known as the Urban Search and Rescue Response System.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="idb559334b-47c4-11f1-9665-b3e99855dc0d" identifier="/us/usc/t6/s722/b"><num value="b" class="bold">(b)</num><heading class="bold"> Authorization of appropriations</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">There is authorized to be appropriated to carry out the system for fiscal year 2008, an amount equal to the amount appropriated for the system for fiscal year 2007 and an additional $20,000,000.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="idb559334c-47c4-11f1-9665-b3e99855dc0d">(<ref href="/us/pl/109/295/tVI/s634">Pub. L. 109–295, title VI, § 634</ref>, <date date="2006-10-04">Oct. 4, 2006</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/120/1421">120 Stat. 1421</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
